A tall illuminated-manuscript style infographic uses a black star-field background with gold borders, serif capitals, and green, amber, blue, and red accent systems. The top third compares three circular “modes of negation” beside a living green branch and a dead red branch; the middle uses flow-line diagrams to show harmful causes being blocked, damped, redirected, or indiscriminately suppressed. Lower panels use symbolic figures such as scales, a question mark, warning triangle, eye-in-triangle, arrows, and checklist marks to frame moral discernment, responsibility, and justice.
